<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="479" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d479">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">Food Administrator’s File</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Food Administrator</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HHC1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hoover</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the British
                                    Ambassador on Special Mission</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_RERDI1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Reading</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-14">
                                        <hi rend="italic">June 14, 1918</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Lord <persName corresp="#p_RERDI1">Reading</persName></hi>: I greatly appreciate the
                                kindliness of your note of June 12 and I shall be honoured indeed to
                                be the guest of His Majesty’s Government.</p>
                            <p>I do not expect to remain in Europe more than a fortnight as I
                                believe that will be sufficient time to discuss food programmes for
                                next year, so far as they can be determined in advance.</p>
                            <p>I have a feeling that a personal conference with the food
                                administrators abroad would enable us to co-ordinate our problems of
                                production, transportation and supply to better advantage than last
                                year, which has been more or less an experimental and
                                experience-gaining period.</p>
                            <p>Yours faithfully,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>[<persName corresp="#p_HHC1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Herbert
                                            Hoover</hi></persName>]</signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>